author: Carl Nolte
title: Waterfront restaurant manages to avoid eviction — for now
text:
Photo: Liz Hafalia, The Chronicle Helen Hayes breaks bread at Sinbad’s in her first visit to the waterfront restaurant in more than a decade. Helen Hayes breaks bread at Sinbad’s in her first visit to the...
Sinbad’s, the colorful San Francisco waterfront bar and restaurant, filed for bankruptcy protection in federal court Wednesday morning — just in time to prevent the sheriff from shutting down the business and padlocking the premises.
